                title: "Relational operator overloading",
                level: "Intermediate",
                summary: "Overloading ==, !=, <, and > to enable direct object comparison and sorting.",
                content: `
                    <h2>Overloading Relational Comparison (<code>==</code>, <code>&lt;</code>)</h2>
                    <div class="code-container">
                        <div class="code-header"><span class="code-lang">relational_overload.cpp</span></div>
                        <pre><code class="language-cpp">bool operator==(const Complex& other) const {
    return (real == other.real && imag == other.imag);
}
bool operator&lt;(const Complex& other) const {
    return (real*real + imag*imag) &lt; (other.real*other.real + other.imag*other.imag);
}</code></pre>
                    </div>
                `
            }
