                summary: "Base class constructors fire first before Derived class constructors across hierarchy tree.",
                content: `
                    <h2>Constructor Execution Order in Inheritance Tree</h2>
                    <p>When initializing a child class object <code>Derived d;</code>, the execution order is:</p>
                    <ol>
                        <li>Base class constructor <code>Base()</code> executes first.</li>
                        <li>Derived class constructor <code>Derived()</code> executes second.</li>
                    </ol>
                    <p>Destructors execute in exact reverse order (<code>~Derived()</code> then <code>~Base()</code>).</p>
                `
            },
