                id: "mod-10-9",
                title: "Virtual base class",
                level: "Advanced",
                summary: "Solving the Diamond Problem (ambiguity from duplicate base instances) using virtual inheritance (<code>virtual public Base</code>).",
                content: `
                    <h2>Solving the Diamond Problem: Virtual Base Classes</h2>
                    <p>If <code>Class B</code> and <code>Class C</code> both inherit from <code>Class A</code>, and <code>Class D</code> inherits from both <code>B</code> and <code>C</code>, <code>D</code> receives two duplicate copies of <code>A</code>'s variables! Using <code>class B : virtual public A</code> ensures only a single shared instance of <code>A</code> is instantiated.</p>
                `
