                    <h2>Generic Programming: Function & Class Templates</h2>
                    <p>Templates allow writing a single algorithmic blueprint (<code>template &lt;typename T&gt;</code>) that the C++ compiler automatically instantiates for <code>int</code>, <code>double</code>, <code>string</code>, or custom classes at compile time.</p>
                    
                    <div class="code-container">
                        <div class="code-header"><span class="code-lang">template_function.cpp</span><button class="copy-code-btn" onclick="app.copyCode(this)">Copy Code</button></div>
                        <pre><code class="language-cpp">#include &lt;iostream&gt;
using namespace std;

template &lt;typename T&gt;
T getMax(T a, T b) {
    return (a &gt; b) ? a : b;
}

int main() {
    cout &lt;&lt; getMax&lt;int&gt;(10, 45) &lt;&lt; endl;       // Instantiates with int -> 45
    cout &lt;&lt; getMax&lt;double&gt;(3.14, 9.81) &lt;&lt; endl; // Instantiates with double -> 9.81
    return 0;
}</code></pre>
